ANARCHIST: Selfish freedom from all authority and codes

Anarchist characters reject all authority and external moral codes.
They follow their own rules, which may or may not resemble any
conventional morality.  They are unpredictable, impulsive, and often
selfish, but they are not inherently cruel.

An Anarchist character does what feels right at the moment.  They may
help a stranger in trouble today and steal from another stranger
tomorrow.  They resent being told what to do and will instinctively
undermine authority figures.  Their behavior is guided by survival,
desire, and whim.

GUIDELINES
  - Does not respect law or authority; ignores both whenever convenient
  - Will lie, cheat, steal, and use violence without hesitation
  - May help or harm innocents depending on mood, circumstances, or
    profit
  - Keeps promises only as long as doing so is convenient
  - Distrusts and resents authority; may undermine even beneficial
    institutions
  - Will work with anyone if the price or entertainment value is right

Anarchist characters are wildfire in the Rifts world: unpredictable and
potentially dangerous.  They might be the rogue D-Bee who joined your
team for reasons known only to them, or the Vagabond who has decided
that the Coalition, the Federation, and the Lord of the Deep are all
equally worthless.

Other characters can never fully trust an Anarchist, but can often rely
on them for as long as mutual interests align.

